Simple nautilus-scripts

Latest version available at: https://github.com/obilodeau/nautilus-scripts

What
====
* `x264-encode.sh`

  Transcode a video file using h264 for video and mp3 for audio. Works with 
  multiple files selected. Shows a progress bar.

  See the source for parameters (currently tuned for home videos done with a 
  picture camera).

* `x264-encode-rotate-right.sh`

  Same as `x264-encode.sh` but also rotates the video by 90 degrees to the
  right.

Install
=======
1. Copy scripts in ~/.gnome2/nautilus-scripts/
2. Make sure they are executable

